description:
Raw data from the diagnostic study ESTRELLA.&nbsp; 

 The primary objective of this study was to estimate the accuracy of five tests - a recombinant antigen- rapid diagnostic test (RDT); a crude antigen-based ELISA (Bordier ELISA);&nbsp;an ELISA based on two recombinant antigens (Strongy Detect ELISA);&nbsp;a modified Baermann method;&nbsp;an in-house real-time PCR for  Strongyloides stercoralis  infection. Secondary objectives were acceptability and feasibility of use in an endemic area. 

 The study was carried out in remote villages of Ecuador

